FBIS3-36674 "drsov027_a_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-027 Document Type:Daily Report 9 Feb 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Vorontsov Prefers UN Control for Sarajevo LD0902092194 Moscow Radio Moscow World Service in English 0800 GMT 9 Feb 94 LD0902092194 Moscow Radio Moscow World Service Language: English Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] Russia's ambassador to the United Nations, Yuliy Vorontsov, has proposed putting Sarajevo, the capital of Bosnia-Herzegovina, under control of a UN administration, instead of hitting air strikes at positions of the Bosnian Serbs around it. After a closed-door meeting of the Security Council, Yuliy Vorontsov said that under the Security Council's resolution, air strikes are possible only as a means of protecting the UN peacekeeping forces, but not as a means of punishing one of the warring Bosnian sides. [passage omitted]
